-- Chelsea Goalkeeper Cech May Miss Start of Season With Torn Calf Muscle
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-07-21T12:50:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/chelsea-goalkeeper-cech-may-miss-start-of-season-with-torn-calf-muscle.html

          
          
             Chelsea goalkeeper Petr Cech may
miss the start of the Premier League season with a torn muscle
in his right calf.  
 Cech, 28, was injured in training yesterday and is expected
to sidelined for a month, Chelsea said on its website. The
Premier League champion opens the season Aug. 14 at home aganst
West Bromwich Albion.  
 Henrique Hilario and Ross Turnbull are the other
goalkeepers in the Chelsea squad.  
          
          


  


        